The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Arjun orders school recce

 New Delhi, Dec. 28: Human resource development minister Arjun Singh has asked senior officials of his ministry to visit the tsunami-ravaged states and assess the damage caused to educational institutions, reports our special correspondent.

 ?The minister wants the damage to be assessed on a priority basis. If necessary, the ministry will give appropriate assistance to the agencies concerned,? said the ministry.

 Singh has already donated Rs 51,000 as his personal contribution to the Prime Minister?s relief fund.

 The minister held a meeting this morning with officials representing the University Grants Commission, Navodaya Vidyalaya Sangathan, National Council for Educational Research and Training, All India Council for Technical Education and the National Council for Teachers? Education.

 But ?the situation will have to become a bit normal before the ministry can assess the impact of the havoc on educational institutions?, an official said.




